Anonymous Thu 02 Mar 2023 04:13:57 No.54773023 Report
Quoted By: >>54773097 >>54773201
>>54772594
Music Fren here. Here are some good flaws to choose from. Could use a combination of them.
>Musician is an elitist and actively prevents certain ideas from being expressed due to reverence for the greats
>Musician takes the craft so seriously that he pushes away his friends and family
>Musician finds such great comfort in song that he/she uses it as a form of escapism while shying away from repairing his real problems
>Musician wants to make it big, but is conflicted because he/she ends up spending more time doing social things than practicing
>Musician wants to make it big, makes huge sacrifices and doesn't make it. The shame of "not being good enough" while still being unable to put an instrument down
>Musican has made it professionally, but writes songs about controversial topics that make him the enemy of certain demographics or the state.
>Musician becomes obsessed with the pipeline and completely loses his/her soul in the corporate game before wondering later how it all went wrong.
>Musician was introduced to music in relation to a culture he/she really doesn't care about, but later grows attracted to a genre of music that his/her culture considers defiant.
